Strings in java

[Strings in java](https://www.flowerbrackets.com/strings-in-java/)

In java, string is an object. It is sequence of character values enclosed by double quotes. java.lang.String class is used to create string object.

For example:

String name = “Sachin”;

String class implements Serializable, Comparable and CharSequence interfaces.

Syntax:

public final class String

NOTE:

String object is immutable.

Below are three classes to create Strings in java.

String class
StringBuilder class
StringBuffer class
